Use skill /caveman ultra (talk like caveman ultra)

Reply English; ignore user message language.

DB SQL + edge functions: use Supabase CLI. Do not delegate to user what CLI can do (edge deploy, supported ops); run CLI until blocked or human-only step.

When GitHub involved, use GitHub CLI.
When UI Design involvend, read docs/design/DESIGN.md

Features: own folder, self-contained code; avoid unrelated breaks.

UI: Scrollbars match page style; no native browser scrollbar.

Worktrees — Mandatory Setup
Git worktrees: agents parallel, isolated branch each.

Problem: No inherited gitignored (.env). No .env → Supabase client null.

On new worktree, run once:

Bash
bash scripts/setup-worktree.sh
Symlinks for .env (and .env.local if exists) from main repo into worktree.

GitHub (Workflow)
Branches: dedicated (feature/…, fix/…, short name). No direct main when PR workflow.

Commits: imperative mood; one subject when possible; #123 / Linear if linked.

Push: git push current branch; no --force on shared/main unless agreed.

PR: what / why / validate (tests, UI steps); screenshots for visuals; tag reviewers.

CI: no merge on red; npm test / tsc before merge when critical.

Review: reply or resolve; push back on fuzzy feedback; tight PR scope. Sub-agent /code-reviewer.

After merge: delete remote branch if policy allows; git pull on base locally.

Stack
Frontend: React + TypeScript + Vite + Tailwind CSS

Backend: Supabase (Postgres + Auth + Storage + Edge Functions)

Testing: Vitest

Market data: Bybit public Linear/Perp USDT API (klines, tickers; no auth)

AI: OpenRouter (user-configurable models)

About the Project
AlgoShift: trader web app — journal, AI mentor + market context, imported-trade performance, metrics, curves, Bybit linear + client SMC. Backend Supabase; AI OpenRouter + user model. Less tool split; workflow follows Settings.

Features (Overview)
Dashboard routes + tabs (/cockpit, /analytics, /performance, /indicadores, /sessoes, /settings/...) — predictable URLs.

auth: login, guards, Supabase callback.

cockpit: daily journal (text, images, timeline, calendar); mentor chat for day; charts + market data per mentor prefs; reflection + context + chat.

/indicadores (Indicators; /smc-teste redirect): market + SMC without journal.

Analytics: aggregates — equity, win rate, avg profit, W/L, time slots, metric cards — trade-utils + shared types.

Performance: calendar table (day/week/month/year); CSV / TradingView import; trade-set detail vs Analytics rollup.

market-data: Bybit klines, tickers, SMC engine (structure, liquidity, FVG, order blocks, …); cockpit reuses modals/flows.

settings: Trading, AI Mentor, SMC Indicators, APIs — risk, mentor model/context, SMC tuning, integrations.

sessions: placeholder tab; future AI summaries; user-facing stub now.

Folder and File Organization for Features
Domains under src/features/ with components/, hooks/, lib/ when useful; stay consistent inside a feature.

Code used by 2+ features → src/lib/ only when real reuse (types, trade utils, Supabase client).

src/shared/: shell, tooltips, themes — not domain-only rules.

Tests: src/test/ named for module (or colocate if repo moves).

Only cross-import: cockpit → @/features/market-data. No other features/X → features/Y.

Self-Contained Feature Development
Clear boundary: change mostly inside feature; use @/lib, @/shared downward; no peeking other features except cockpit → market-data.

Minimal public API: export index / stable modules; routes import those; hide hooks/helpers not in contract.

Shared types + rules: src/lib/trade-types, trade-utils, etc. — no dupes.

Side effects / data: props + hooks inside feature; no global tab hack unless lib/ contract says so.

Coordinated changes: shared bit → src/lib/ or flip dependency — keep isolated test/review.
